[1]The Sacred Tunic (in German-Der Heilige Rock) is a relic conserved in the cathedral of Trier, and consisting of a piece of cloth that is believed to have been part of the tunic that he wore Christ before his crucifixion and, according to the Gospel of St. John, the roman soldiers in charge of the surveillance of the scaffold is held by pulling at the fate.
[2]The verse quoted by the Evangelist is that of the Book of Psalms 22 (21), 19 The authenticity of the Holy Robe is controversial.
[3]Its changing history and the sometimes adverse storage conditions did cause that they should proceed to an examination of archaeological textiles between 1973 and 1974, which, however, failed to define the exact origin and age of the find.Ursula Bartmann: Kleiner Reiseführer zum Heiligen Rock; Seite 69-75.
